Photo by NYJFO ✈️ on August 19, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, playing football and text that says '@NYJETSFANSONLY HLANTIC NEW YORK 19 JETS INJURY UPDATE UPDATE CARL LAWSON OUT FOR SEASON'.

node.text: The Jets officially announced that Carl Lawson will miss the season after suffering a torn achilles in today’s joint practice. Brutal blow to the defense, probably the best performer in camp and was set for a breakout year. Just terrible. #Jets #CarlLawson

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by NYJFO ✈️ on August 18, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Rich Cimini @RichCimini @NYJETSFANSONLY G Alex Lewis has decided to retire, per source. Was eliminated from playing for any team in 2021 last week when #Jets placed him on reserve/left squad list. In theory, could try comeback in '22, but it remains to be seen whether he has any desire to play again, source said. NEW 71 YORK'.

node.text: Jets OL Alex Lewis has decided to hang up the cleats and retire. He was placed on the exempt/left squad list a couple weeks ago and was given time away from the team as he dealt with things “bigger than football.” Wishing him all the best. 🙏 #Jets #AlexLewis

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by NYJFO ✈️ on August 17, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, playing football and text that says '@NYJETSFANSONLY NEWYORK ROSTER CUTS'.

node.text:
The Jets made 4 moves to trim their roster down to 85 players ahead of the 4 PM deadline:
——
Waived: 
S Bennett Jackson
DL Michael Dwumfour
RB Austin Walter

Placed on IR:
OL Cam Clark
——
Next cut deadline is to 80 players next Tuesday, followed by the final 53 man roster cuts on August 31st. #Jets
